    <p class="about">
      <strong>About Astro</strong>
      Astro is a content-focused framework that ships zero JavaScript by default, using an "islands"
      architecture where interactive components hydrate independently. Pros: outstanding Core Web Vitals,
      framework-agnostic (React, Vue, Svelte all work), purpose-built for content-heavy sites.
      Cons: smaller ecosystem than Next.js, client-side features require explicit island opt-in,
      not suited for full-stack or highly dynamic applications.
    </p>
  </div>
